cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image processing and specifically with despeckling of SAR images using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves statistical analysis and optimization of a cost function, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of simulated data and the validation on both real and simulated data could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
